refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringfalseiconv stringfrom_encoding stringto_encoding stringstring
Converts string from from_encoding to to_encoding.

&reftitle.notes;



  The character encodings and options available depend on the installed implementation
  of iconv. If the argument to from_encoding
  or to_encoding is not supported on the current system, &false;
  will be returned.

  &reftitle.examples;



    iconv example


<?php
$text = "This is the Euro symbol '€'.";

echo 'Original : ', $text, PHP_EOL;
echo 'TRANSLIT : ', iconv("UTF-8", "ISO-8859-1//TRANSLIT", $text), PHP_EOL;
echo 'IGNORE   : ', iconv("UTF-8", "ISO-8859-1//IGNORE", $text), PHP_EOL;
echo 'Plain    : ', iconv("UTF-8", "ISO-8859-1", $text), PHP_EOL;

?>


    &example.outputs.similar;


Original : This is the Euro symbol '€'.
TRANSLIT : This is the Euro symbol 'EUR'.
IGNORE   : This is the Euro symbol ''.
Plain    :
Notice: iconv(): Detected an illegal character in input string in .\iconv-example.php on line 7
